# CYBER SENTINELS App

Trust infrastructure for humans, AI agents, and digital systems.

This is the Next.js / Vercel product app for CYBER SENTINELS.

## Core Routes

```text
/
/dashboard
/verify-human
/trust-graph
/agent-passport
/api/health
/api/audit
/api/world-id/verify
```

## Tech Stack

* Next.js 14 App Router
* TypeScript
* Tailwind CSS
* Vercel
* Postgres / Neon / Vercel Postgres
* World ID proof-of-human integration

## Folder Structure

```text
app/
  api/
    audit/
      route.ts
    health/
      route.ts
    world-id/
      verify/
        route.ts
  agent-passport/
    page.tsx
  dashboard/
    page.tsx
  trust-graph/
    page.tsx
  verify-human/
    page.tsx
  globals.css
  layout.tsx
  page.tsx

lib/
  db.ts
  world-id.ts

db/
  schema.sql
```

## Environment Variables

Create `.env.local` locally and add the same values in Vercel Project Settings.

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://username:password@host:5432/cybersentinels
WORLD_RP_ID=cybersentinels
WORLD_SIGNING_KEY=your_signing_key_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_WORLD_APP_ID=app_staging_xxxxx
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
NODE_ENV=development
```

## Database Setup

Run the SQL in:

```text
db/schema.sql
```

This creates:

* `verified_humans`
* `agent_passports`
* `audit_logs`

## Local Development

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open:

```text
http://localhost:3000
```

## Production Build

```bash
npm run build
npm run start
```

## Vercel Settings

Use:

```text
Framework Preset: Next.js
Install Command: npm install
Build Command: npm run build
Output Directory: leave blank
```

## World ID Integration

World ID is used as the proof-of-human signal.

Cyber Sentinels adds:

* trust scoring
* audit logging
* nullifier replay protection
* enterprise verification decisions
* future device/session intelligence

Verification route:

```text
POST /api/world-id/verify
```

## Security Notes

* Keep `WORLD_SIGNING_KEY` server-side only.
* Never expose database credentials in frontend code.
* Store World ID nullifier hashes to prevent replay.
* Use audit logs for every high-trust decision.
* Add production-grade rate limiting before public launch.

## Founder Positioning

Cyber Sentinels is not just identity verification.

It is trust infrastructure for a world where humans are no longer distinguishable from machines.
